                            <comment id="75096" author="dmiter" created="Thu, 16 Jan 2014 16:54:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;fix is &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/8883&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/8883&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="73200" author="bogl" created="Tue, 10 Dec 2013 16:10:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just to provide a little more detail I encountered this problem when trying to do builds for the new 6.5 release.  As ldiskfs support is still in a state of flux for that kernel I need to build without ldiskfs for test purposes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I believe I have confirmed this problem is a recent thing.  I can configure and build rpms from b2_4 --without-ldiskfs on Centos 6.5 just fine.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
